    "title": {
      "rendered": "Four Reasons Why Your Nonprofit Should Pay More Attention to LinkedIn Pages in 2017"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Why-Your-Nonprofit-Should-Use-LinkedIn-Facebook.jpg\"><br />\n<img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-20771\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Why-Your-Nonprofit-Should-Use-LinkedIn-Facebook-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Why-Your-Nonprofit-Should-Use-LinkedIn-Facebook.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Why-Your-Nonprofit-Should-Use-LinkedIn-Facebook.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Why-Your-Nonprofit-Should-Use-LinkedIn-Facebook.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Why-Your-Nonprofit-Should-Use-LinkedIn-Facebook.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Why-Your-Nonprofit-Should-Use-LinkedIn-Facebook.jpg?w=650&amp;ssl=1 650w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>Odds are your nonprofit has a <strong><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company-beta/509171/\">LinkedIn Page</a></strong>.\u00a0Most nonprofits have claimed their pages and set up the basics,\u00a0but very few regularly post on their LinkedIn Pages. Snapchat and Instagram may be all the buzz, but ignoring LinkedIn Pages is a mistake. In addition the reasons listed below, the <a href=\"http://www.pewinternet.org/2016/11/11/social-media-update-2016/\"><strong>demographics of LinkedIn users</strong></a>\u00a0bodes well for engaging donors and amazingly LinkedIn offers customer service. If you have questions or concerns, there&#8217;s a real human being available to respond to your inquiries and that&#8217;s rare in the social media space. Thanks LinkedIn!</p>\n<h2>1. LinkedIn Pages have a new design.</h2>\n<p>Still in beta for most, LinkedIn is slowly rolling out a new\u00a0design for Pages, Admin Tools, the News Feed, and LinkedIn Profiles. Clearly, LinkedIn has big plans for 2017.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company-beta/509171/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20754\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedinPage.png?resize=600%2C323\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"323\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedinPage.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedinPage.png?resize=300%2C162&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company-beta/509171/\">linkedin.com/company/nonprofitorgs</a></h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">2. Engagement and/or click-throughs are often higher on LinkedIn Pages than on Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram.</h2>\n<p>Compared to Facebook and Twitter, Nonprofit Tech for Good gets more likes, click-throughs, and comments from its\u00a0<strong><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company-beta/509171/\">3,596 LinkedIn Followers</a></strong> (proportionally speaking) than from its\u00a0<strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pg/nonprofitorgs/\">100,708 Facebook Followers</a></strong> and <strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/nonprofitorgs\">841,619 Twitter Follower</a>s</strong>. Nonprofit Tech for Good does get more likes on Instagram, but Instagram has the lowest click-through rate of all social media with only 11 visits from its\u00a0<strong><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/nonprofitorgs/\">45,800 Instagram Followers</a></strong> last week.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.womensmarch.com/100\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-20757 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Click-Throughs.png?resize=500%2C549\" width=\"500\" height=\"549\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Click-Throughs.png?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Click-Throughs.png?resize=273%2C300&amp;ssl=1 273w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>3. LinkedIn Analytics are detailed and insightful.</h2>\n<p>LinkedIn Analytics are straight-forward and detailed. They tell you exactly how many people clicked on your links and the percent of engagement received in proportion to your number of followers, neither of which are available in Facebook Insights or Twitter Analytics.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company-beta/509171/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20760\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Analytics-1.png?resize=600%2C336\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"336\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Analytics-1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Analytics-1.png?resize=300%2C168&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company-beta/509171/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-20761 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Analytics-2.png?resize=600%2C336\" width=\"600\" height=\"336\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Analytics-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Analytics-2.png?resize=300%2C168&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">4. The LinkedIn Admin Tools have been simplified to focus on the most important features of LinkedIn Pages.</h2>\n<p>Less is more in the case of the new LinkedIn Admin Tools. The focus is on layout, design, search, language, posting, and analytics to maximize how page content is presented in the News Feed.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company-beta/509171/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20764\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Admin-Pages.png?resize=600%2C262\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"262\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Admin-Pages.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/LinkedIn-Admin-Pages.png?resize=300%2C131&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mobile-for-good-look-inside.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
